description:
This market refers to the LoL match between Hanwha Life Esports and T1 in the LCK Cup Group Stage, scheduled for January 16 at 5:30AM ET.

This market will resolve to "Hanwha Life Esports" if Hanwha Life Esports secures the most inhibitors across all games in the match. 

This market will resolve to "T1" if T1 secures the most inhibitors across all games in the match.

If both teams secure the same number of inhibitors across all games in the match, this market will resolve 50-50.

If the match is canceled (not played at all), ends in a tie, or is delayed beyond 7 days from the scheduled date without a winner determined, this market will resolve to 50-50. 

If the match begins but is not completed, and one team wins due to the opponent's forfeiture, disqualification, or walkover, this market will resolve to 50-50. 

If the match ends in a forfeit, disqualification, or walkover (team withdraws before the start and the other wins automatically), this market will resolve to 50-50.

events.description:
This market will resolve to "Hanwha Life Esports" if Hanwha Life Esports win against T1 in the named LoL match in the LCK Cup Group Stage, scheduled for January 16 at 5:30AM ET.

This market will resolve to "T1" if T1 win against Hanwha Life Esports in the LoL match.

If the game is postponed, this market will remain open until the game has been completed.

If the game is canceled entirely, with no make-up game, this market will resolve 50-50.

The resolution source for this market will be official information from https://liquipedia.net/leagueoflegends/Main_Page.
events.title: LoL: Hanwha Life Esports vs T1 (BO3) - LCK Cup Group Stage
